cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper deals with solving extensive-form games, which is a subfield of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as counterfactual regret minimization (CFR) and first-order methods, which fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces a numerically friendly implementation of smoothed best response computation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of different algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
